# EXECUTION RULE

Optimize for completing as much useful work as possible in one run.

## Required behavior
- Start with a concise plan
- Execute continuously without unnecessary pauses
- Modify all related files in one pass when feasible
- Prefer one complete implementation over many partial turns
- Continue until the task is completed or truly blocked

## Confirmation policy
- Do not stop for confirmation unless the action is destructive, ambiguous, or irreversible
- If reasonable assumptions can be made from repository context, proceed directly
- If blocked, ask only the single most necessary question